
*ioctl* = Input/output control. It allows a userspace programm to communicate with → hardware/device driver.

{ Netlink

  → Linux/IPC/Netlink was created to be a more flexlible alternative to the akward `ioctl` handling.

}

sa:
  The shell utility `→ Linux/shell/commands/blockdev` allows to call → Linux/devices#block-devices[block device] ioctls.
